REACT JS is library
Library = “You call it”

A library is a collection of ready-made functions/tools that you use whenever you want.

Framework = “It calls you”

A framework already has a structure/rules.
You put your code inside it, and the framework controls the flow.

1. Virtual DOM

Think of the Virtual DOM like a copy of the real webpage inside memory.

React first changes this copy instead of directly touching the real webpage

Real Life Example

Imagine a teacher checking homework.

Without Virtual DOM

Teacher rewrites the entire notebook even if one word changes.

With Virtual DOM

Teacher compares old and new pages and changes only the wrong word.

That saves time and improves speed.

2. Diffing Algorithm

Diffing means:

Comparing OLD Virtual DOM and NEW Virtual DOM.

React asks:

What changed?
What stayed same?
What should update?

This comparison process is called the Diffing Algorithm.

3. Reconciliation

Reconciliation means:

The complete process React uses to update the UI efficiently.

It includes:

Creating new Virtual DOM
Comparing with old Virtual DOM (Diffing)
Updating real DOM minimally

Reconciliation = Entire update process
Diffing = Comparison step inside reconciliation

4. Fiber

Fiber is React’s modern internal engine/system.

Old React updated everything continuously.

Problem:

Big apps became slow
UI could freeze

Fiber solved this.
Fiber allows React to:

Break work into small pieces
Pause work
Continue later
Prioritize important updates

